Passing parameters to the route is done with the following syntax:

    {{ route(&#39;info.update&#39;, [&#39;id&#39; =&gt; $info-&gt;id]) }}

Second to this, your controller should expect to receive the `$id`:

    public function method(Request $request, $id)
    {
    
        // logic
    }

Last, you must make sure that your route is expecting the `id` by using the `{id}` option within your route helper. An example would be:

    Route::get(&#39;model/{id}&#39;, &#39;ModelController@store&#39;);

I hope this helps.

